ReviewText:
I have super pale lips and this is great for a natural, buildable lip stain. It's a bit drying but the color stays when I put chapstick over it which is awesome. Worked fine for me as a natural-looking blush too. 

The formula is VERY watery. The first time I applied on my lips I put too much on and it actually got on my teeth and stained them until I brushed them (came right off with a good toothbrushing). So be careful if you're out otherwise you will look like you just drank a bottle of red wine - not cute. Better to slowly and carefully build color with a smaller amount of product.

ReviewText:
A blush but better! 
My first time using a blush tint and my first impression I’m super impressed and loving them. 

Easy to use applicator, great size doe foot for precise application, great lightweight formula that blends seamlessly into the skin giving me a pretty flush of color to my cheeks and love how natural it looks. I love that it’s sheer but you can build it up to your liking. 
A little truly goes a long way! 

I tried all 3 shades Rosy, Pink-lemonade and Fiery-red tint and my favorite is Pink-lemonade. I’ve attached swatches of all 3 shades below so you can see how they look on me. 

It’s the perfect shade for my medium brown skin and suits me well. It looks as if I’m blushing naturally whenever I wear this blush, which i find super cute. I also like to apply it on my lips giving me the perfect subtle pink shade without drying my lips, almost mimics my lip natural lip color but better.  I apply two small dots and then dab with my fingers. It blends super quick and easy which is great for mums like me that are always on the go and need a quick makeup. Also didn’t have to worry about it rubbing off throughout the day as it’s long-wearing and does not smudge 

A great addition to my everyday makeup look. Highly recommend them!
